@blanuk You can indeed set a Titan to TCC in Windows:

There's an nvidia tool in: C:\Program Files\NVIDIA Corporation\NVSMI

nvidia-smi.exe -L

to list graphics adapters in the system.

and:

nvidia-smi.exe -g 0 -dm 1

to enable tcc mode on adapter 0.  -dm 0 to turn it off.  You'll have to reboot for it to change.

What do you mean by you "increased your swap under windows to 200gb"?  What
is swap?  I have a titan 24gb too.  Was wondering how to make it as
efficient as possible.  Also, did you set it to TCC?  Did that make a
difference?  Thanks!
